: contemporary translations of the New Testament gospels; audio-recorded transcribed and glossed texts; and elicited material collected with a range of speakers. The analysis includes comparisons with other Malakula languages and is both of typological and historical-comparative interest. The data documentation is substantial and detailed.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aEndangered languagesvMalekula (Vanuatu) 0aEndangered languageszVanuatuzMalekula. 0aMalekulavLanguages 0aUnua languagevGrammar. 0aUnua languagexGrammar. 4aEndangered Languages. 4aOceanic Languages. 4aVanuatu, Malakula. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2015z9783110438710oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97815015005100 cprintz978161451765840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978161451659040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781614516590423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781614516590.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DSPb2015